Content: [dscrdeql] <NWhiskeyTango> Would a pool for mining EQLI be a positive thing for the project?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <Llama-Admin> I don't know how that would affect it. The mining reward is super small, and we are implementing masternodes soon.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <NWhiskeyTango> True. I mean a pool won't take over the network with dPOW. I am just trying to figure what the positives would be and I find none

Author: Gateway#3763

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <NWhiskeyTango> -pool would have a "fee"

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <NWhiskeyTango> -pool would earn most of the block rewards

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <NWhiskeyTango> - people would spend more on electricity trying to fight for the highest share % on pool

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <NWhiskeyTango> -other "solo" miners would be EVEN less "profitable"

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <Biomech-Founder> the block reward, currently, is .0001 EQL per block. This is going to go away. It was an error in the code. We MIGHT keep it, but probably not. By running a full node with gen=true in your EQL.conf, you ARE mining and you will get the transaction fees.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <Biomech-Founder> In our design, we deliberately wanted to avoid the problems associated with pools.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <Biomech-Founder> You can set one up, easily, but it's not going to be profitable, unless you and your friends wanted to form a private one to pool cheap hardware. Even then, I don't see it being worthwhile.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <Biomech-Founder> I could be wrong, as things progress, but I'm thinking smart contracts will be where the profit lies üòÑ

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <NWhiskeyTango> With all these facts i just see it hurting to have a pool more then helping. Do you all agree?

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <Biomech-Founder> Yeah. I see exactly one exception, and it's only personal use.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <Biomech-Founder> If you got a bunch of computers or old equipment that can mine, making your own pool might help your chances of processing transactions.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <Biomech-Founder> But outside of that, I really don't see a use case. Especially for a public pool.

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <Biomech-Founder> I've run several pools. Hell, I'm running one now üòÑ But I don't see the point for this one.
